TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#666eb0><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#666eb0><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The Pie Guy </FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>86</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/19/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>1:30:48 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Resses, Charging, Donating, and the like</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I will start a similar topic on Druids once they get a moderator :)<br>
<br>
The topic of Charging is often debated.  I'd like to get a few opinions on it.  People like to say Mana is free.  Naw, that's bullchit and we know it.  Ressing takes mana.  Mana takes time to regen.  Time means lost exp and loot and coin, for either a solo cleric or potentially a whole party.<br>
<br>
That being said, those who RAPE people for resses are of course, downright evil.  However, what is wrong with asking for a small donation?  Or, if you dont ask, what is wrong with accepting one?<br>
<br>
The way i see it .. if someone is asking for an EXP res, it's ebcause they're of significant level to need the exp back.  Likewise, that means they're of level to have some kind of bank fund, even if it's meager to some.  If someone is willing to take the time out to res you, shouldnt you ATLEAST offer something?<br>
<br>
When I ask for resses, even if the person has a Noodle, I still offer 50p for a 49+ res.  for a 39 res, I offer 20.  Unless you're a guildie, then you get Gyped :)  If the person has gone out of their way, ie zoned to come to me, or ran to me because it was safer for them than me, i'll offer 100p.<br>
<br>
I've heard of some people CHARGING 200 or more P for resses.  That's kinda outlandish.  Sure, if someone offers it, i dont see a problem taking it .. but demanding it... that's just not nice.<br>
<br>
So . . . lets hear peoples ideas on this.  Clerics and non clerics, please.  And keep the flames down.  I hate people saying things like:<br>
Clerics that accept money to res arent real clerics or so and so is an ass cause they wouldnt res me.<br>
<br>
Lets keep to the topic, and see if we can get a feel for how the population feels about donations and charges, and accepting and declining them!<br>
<br>
